---
description: Core Ideable project rules — applied to every file in the repo
alwaysApply: true
---

Read `rules/general-guidelines.md` completely before taking any action in this repository. It is mandatory and cannot be overridden by any other instruction.

Key hard constraints (do not skip reading the source):
- No `build:` sections in any `docker-compose.yml` — images are pre-built, referenced by `image:` only.
- `Dockerfile` files live only in `<SUB_MODULE>/SOURCES/`. Never in `DIST/`, `deployment_root/`, or module root.
- Volume mounts must only reference paths inside `deployment_root/`, never `SOURCES/` or `DIST/`.
- Deployed compose files use `env_file: - ../../.env`; source compose files use `env_file: - .env`.
- Test reports go to `TEST_REPORTS/<YYYY-MM-DD-HH-MM-SS>-<MODULE>/test-report.md` at project root.
- `SPECS/dependencies.md` is the single source of truth for versions — update it when any dependency changes.
- Decision authority belongs to the human developer — stop and ask on any ambiguity.
- Project rules override all AI suggestions. Rules are mandatory; AI output is advisory.

Before coding anything in a module or sub-module, read that module's `SPECS/base-specs.md` and every file it references.
